Mauritius Post and Cooperative Bank
Ltd., a state-owned lender, said net income for the 12 months
through December increased 12 percent as revenue climbed.  Net income advanced to 102.6 million rupees ($3.6 million)
while revenue rose 17 percent to 854.5 million rupees, the bank
said in a statement published in the Port Louis-based Le Matinal
newspaper today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
